# Portal CI Gates & Quality Enforcement

These gates prevent architectural drift in the Supplier Portal. They supplement
the existing 32 gates in `tools/scripts/gate-*.mjs`.

---

## Existing gates (already enforced — portal inherits all 32)

### Structural gates (portal-critical)

| Gate                      | What it checks                                                                    | Script                        | Portal impact                                                  |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `gate:web-module`         | Every `page.tsx` has sibling `loading.tsx`                                        | `gate-web-module.mjs`         | All `(supplier-portal)` pages must comply                      |
| `gate:db-module`          | Every tenant table has RLS + policy                                               | `gate-db-module.mjs`          | All `portal-*` tables need `tenant_id` + RLS                   |
| `gate:identity-sot`       | No raw `x-tenant-id` / `x-user-id` header reads                                   | `gate-identity-sot.mjs`       | Portal routes must use `PortalRequestContext`, not raw headers |
| `gate:status-types`       | Status fields use union types, not bare `string`                                  | `gate-status-types.mjs`       | Portal enums must use typed unions                             |
| `gate:kernel-invariants`  | Auth guards on routes, kernel context usage                                       | `gate-kernel-invariants.mjs`  | Extend for `@afenda/supplier-kernel` boundary                  |
| `gate:schema-conventions` | Drizzle: `.enableRLS()`, `tenantCol()`, `pkId()`, `timestamps()`, `moneyBigint()` | `gate-schema-conventions.mjs` | Portal tables must follow all SC-01 through SC-08              |

