## Agent CI awareness

When writing portal code, agents must be aware:

1. **Before creating a new portal file** — check if an existing SP code covers
   it. If not, assign the next available SP code in the appropriate series.
2. **Before merging any feature** — Phase 0 (kernel) must be green. Check
   `portal-registry.ts` for SP-1001 through SP-1010 status.
3. **After editing a portal service** — run `pnpm typecheck` + relevant gate
   locally before committing.
4. **After adding a new DB table** — ensure `tenant_id` + RLS policy exist
   (`gate-db-module.mjs` will catch this, but fix pre-commit).
5. **After adding a new page** — ensure `loading.tsx` + `error.tsx` siblings
   exist (`gate-web-module.mjs` will catch this).

