## ESLint rules inherited by portal code

Portal files inherit rules from three layers:

### Layer 1: `@afenda/eslint-config` (base — all `.ts`/`.tsx`)

| Rule                                         | Severity | What                                                            |
| -------------------------------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`          | error    | No unused vars (ignores `_`-prefixed)                           |
| `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` | error    | Must use `import type` for type-only imports                    |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`         | warn     | Avoid `any` — use `unknown` or specific types                   |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-non-null-assertion`   | warn     | No `!` — use optional chaining or guards                        |
| `no-console`                                 | warn     | Only `console.warn`/`console.error` allowed                     |
| **CIG-04** `no-restricted-imports`           | error    | Routes/pages cannot import `@afenda/db`, `drizzle-orm` directly |

### Layer 2: `apps/web/eslint.config.js` (frontend-specific)

| Rule / Selector                        | Severity | What                                          |
| -------------------------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| **RBP-03** `.sort()` ban               | warn     | Use `.toSorted()` — immutable sort            |
| **RBP-CACHE** async export fetcher ban | warn     | Server data fetchers must use `cache()`       |
| `Date.now()` in render                 | warn     | Hydration risk — use `useEffect + useState`   |
| `Math.random()` in render              | warn     | Hydration risk — use `useId()` for stable IDs |
| `console.log`                          | warn     | Use pino logging, not console.log             |
| `react/jsx-key`                        | error    | Every array element needs a key               |
| `react/no-array-index-key`             | error    | Use stable IDs, not array index               |
| `react-hooks/rules-of-hooks`           | error    | Hooks at top level only                       |
| `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`          | warn     | All effect dependencies must be listed        |
| `jsx-a11y/*`                           | mixed    | Full accessibility ruleset                    |
| `eqeqeq`                               | error    | `===` required (except null)                  |
| `prefer-destructuring`                 | error    | Object destructuring preferred                |

### Layer 3: `packages/modules/finance/eslint.config.js` (services/routes)

| Rule / Selector                       | Severity | What                                                         |
| ------------------------------------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **CIG-02** `Number()` in `*`          | error    | No float math on money — use `convertAmountPrecise` / BigInt |
| **CIG-02** `parseFloat()` in `*`      | error    | Same — no float-based currency conversion                    |
| **CIG-02** `Math.round(x * rate)`     | error    | Same — use BigInt fixed-point                                |
| **CIG-03** `req.query as Record`      | error    | Use Zod schema `.parse()` for input validation               |
| **CIG-03** `req.params` cast          | error    | Use `IdParamSchema.parse()` or Zod schema                    |
| **CIG-04** Tests outside `__tests__/` | error    | Test files must be inside `__tests__/` directories           |

