## Portal-specific ESLint rules (to be added in Phase 0)

These use `no-restricted-imports` and `no-restricted-syntax` patterns in
`packages/eslint-config/index.js` (or a portal-specific config overlay).

### ESLINT-PORTAL-01: No direct identity resolution in services

```javascript
// Add to portal route/service files
'no-restricted-syntax': ['error', {
  selector: "CallExpression[callee.name='resolveSupplierIdentity']",
  message: 'SP-IDENTITY-01: Use PortalRequestContext from preHandler hook, not resolveSupplierIdentity() directly.',
}]
```

### ESLINT-PORTAL-02: No raw internal status labels in portal frontend

```javascript
// Add to (supplier-portal) files
'no-restricted-syntax': ['error', {
  selector: "Literal[value=/FRAUD_SUSPICION|SANCTIONS_HIT|AML_REVIEW|INTERNAL_HOLD/]",
  message: 'SP-LANG-01: Internal hold reasons must not appear in portal code. Use Status Dictionary.',
}]
```

### ESLINT-PORTAL-03: Kernel cannot import from AP module

```javascript
// Add to packages/supplier-kernel/ config
'no-restricted-imports': ['error', {
  patterns: [{
    group: ['@afenda/modules/*', '@afenda/modules/finance', '@afenda/modules/finance/*'],
    message: 'SP-IMPORT-01: Kernel must not import from module packages. Use ports/contracts only.',
  }]
}]
```

These supplement existing ESLint config. Add them incrementally during
Phase 0 kernel buildout.
